### Multi-Tenant SaaS API - Feature Flags
### VS Code REST Client / JetBrains HTTP Client compatible

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@contentType = application/json

### Get tokens first by running auth.http login
@accessToken = {{$dotenv %ACCESS_TOKEN}}
@tenantId = {{$dotenv %TENANT_ID}}

### Get all feature flags for current tenant
GET {{baseUrl}}/feature-flags
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenantId}}

### List flags with details (requires settings.read permission)
GET {{baseUrl}}/feature-flags/list
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenantId}}

### Check if a specific feature is enabled
GET {{baseUrl}}/feature-flags/new_dashboard/check
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenantId}}

### Create a tenant-specific override
POST {{baseUrl}}/feature-flags/overrides
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenantId}}

{
  "key": "beta_features",
  "name": "Beta Features",
  "description": "Enable beta features for this tenant",
  "enabled": true,
  "metadata": {
    "rollout_percentage": 100
  }
}

### Update a tenant-specific override
PUT {{baseUrl}}/feature-flags/overrides/beta_features
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenantId}}

{
  "enabled": false,
  "name": "Beta Features (Disabled)"
}

### Toggle a feature flag
POST {{baseUrl}}/feature-flags/overrides/beta_features/toggle
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenantId}}

### Delete a tenant override (falls back to global)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/feature-flags/overrides/beta_features
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenantId}}
